//PHP USB PRINTER
Hey,

I often refer to "https://mike42.me/blog/2015-03-getting-a-usb-receipt-printer-working-on-linux" blog post when I talk about Linux USB.

Your next debugging steps are along the lines of-

sudo usermod -a -G lp habibridho (Add yourself, and your web user to the lp group)
lsmod | grep usblp (confirm that usblp is loaded. if not, make it load!)
ls /dev/usb/ (find the device. If not, replug it and debug with dmesg)
echo "test" >> /dev/usb/ABC" (where "ABC" is the name of your printer, found in the last step)
Once you have this working on the command-line, you are ready to use new FilePrintConector("/dev/usb/ABC") to start printing with escpos-php.

//php usb printer
https://mike42.me/blog/2015-03-getting-a-usb-receipt-printer-working-on-linux